// skeleton/maps/skeleton.map
//
// Smallest sealed Valve220 map this engine can dmap and load.
// One 512x512x256 room formed by six axis-aligned slab brushes
// (floor, ceiling, four walls), one info_player_start, one light.
//
// All brushes use textures/common/caulk so the dmap pass treats the
// room as a sealed structural area without doing any visual work.
// Replace caulk on the inner faces with your own materials once the
// engine is up and rendering.
//
// Coordinate convention (id Tech): +Z is up, units are inches/world
// units. Three plane points per face are listed so that
//   normal = (p1 - p2) x (p3 - p2)
// faces OUTWARD from the brush, matching what idPlane::FromPoints
// expects in src/idlib/math/Plane.h.

// entity 0 — worldspawn
{
"classname" "worldspawn"
